Kneading motion by grasping your skin with your thumb and fingers and massaging it in circular motion like it was dough. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/50/Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/50/Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pinch the skin gently between thumb and fingers and pull it slightly away from the body. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8d/Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8d/Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Do-Anti-Cellulite-Massage-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

